1
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:03,080
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

2
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:38,280
(WHISTLING)

3
00:00:44,440 --> 00:00:46,440
-Hey, you.
-Hey!

4
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,120
Listen, can we talk?

5
00:00:53,360 --> 00:00:54,680
Rory!

6
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:58,640
No, shut up.
I've just got a question, that's all.

7
00:00:58,840 --> 00:01:02,240
-You okay up there?
-Yeah, fine. No problem.

8
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:06,000
-What are you doing?
-Helping the Doctor. Um, it's humming.

9
00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:07,760
-Is that okay?
-Yeah, it's fine.

10
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:09,360
We're just entering conceptual space.

11
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:11,800
Imagine a banana or anything curved...
Actually don't,

12
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:14,720
"cause it's not curved or like a banana.
Forget the banana!

13
00:01:14,880 --> 00:01:16,640
Uh, is he helping you fly the Tardis?

14
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:21,080
Attach thermo couplings two,
seven and 11,

15
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:22,560
like I showed you.

16
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:24,800
How come he gets a go?
You never let me have a go.

17
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,560
RORY: Uh, Doctor, don't.

18
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:30,320
-Seriously, I let her drive my car once.
-Yeah, to the end of the road!

19
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:33,920
Where, according to Amy,
there was an "unexpected house".

20
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:36,880
Oh, he's jealous because I passed
my test first time.

21
00:01:36,960 --> 00:01:39,360
-You cheated. You wore a skirt.
-I didn't wear a skirt.

22
00:01:40,040 --> 00:01:42,040
-Well, luck would have worked, too.
-No, no,

23
00:01:42,280 --> 00:01:44,640
I did wear a skirt,
but it was any old skirt.

24
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:46,520
-You ever seen Amy drive, Doctor?
-No.

25
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:49,040
Neither did her driving examiner.

26
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:51,680
Actually, it was this one.
It was this skirt!

27
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:53,480
(CRASHING)

28
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:01,760
-What was that?
-Rory!

29
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:04,640
Did you drop a thermo coupling?

30
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:08,000
-Sorry.
-Ah! How did you do that?

31
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:09,680
I told you, "Don't drop them.”

32
00:02:09,760 --> 00:02:11,440
I specifically mentioned
not dropping them.

33
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:13,880
-It was my fault.
-Of course it wasn't your fault.

34
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:16,400
-It kind of was her fault.
-How could it be her fault?

35
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:19,760
Because it was my skirt
and my husband and your glass floor.

36
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:23,760
Oh, Rory!

37
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:25,960
-Sorry.
-Well, we've landed.

38
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:28,000
Emergency materialisation.
It should be fine,

39
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:29,880
should have locked onto the
safest space available.

40
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:31,720
(ELECTRICAL BUZZING)

41
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:53,840
AMY: Doctor, what's happened?

42
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:59,240
The safest spot available. The Tardis
has materialised inside itself.

43
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:02,160
-Is that supposed to happen?
-Take a guess.

44
00:03:03,640 --> 00:03:05,960
RORY: No?
DOCTOR: That's the one.

45
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:08,320
Whoa, what are you doing?

46
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,800
I have absolutely no idea.

47
00:03:16,040 --> 00:03:18,040
Okay, that is a bit weird.

48
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:25,640
-That is actually pretty cool.
-Oh, I'm glad you're entertained, Rory.

49
00:03:25,760 --> 00:03:28,440
Now that we're stuck here for all
eternity, at least you won't be bored.

50
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:29,560
Wait, what? We're stuck?

51
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:32,040
The inside of the Tardis is now joined
to the outside of the Tardis.

52
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:34,000
Worse than a time loop, a space loop.

53
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:38,000
Nothing can enter or leave this ship
ever again.

54
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:39,360
(DOOR OPENING)

55
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:45,120
Okay, kids,
this is where it gets complicated.

